      <context>
         <note type="warning">
            <ul>
               <li>If lifting rope breaks, serious injury/damage may occur.</li>
               <li>The lifting wire rope and stay must be long enough to avoid
              contact with the forklift. Short rope/stay can damage the vehicle.
              If it's too long, it may cause interference.</li>
               <li>Cover the rope/chain with rubber or cloth to prevent damage to
              the vehicle, as necessary.</li>
               <li>Rope/chain and other lifting tools must have sufficient
              strength, and free of any defect or wear.</li>
               <li>Avoid impact load to the lifting devices/tools.</li>
            </ul>
         </note>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Check the weight, length, width and height of the vehicle
before lifting.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Park the crane at an appropriate position.</p>
         </li>
